      "writtenOn": "2017-11-11T02:05:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I did the math and this makes sense, with one possible robustness change (that you can take or not take, your choice).\n\nInstead of transforming to the world-space position, transform relative to the camera first, then project that ray out to the object distance, and convert that point from camera-local to world space:\n\n    const glm::vec3 cameraSpaceNearPlaneCoordinate \u003d\n            glm::inverse(mPerspective) * screenSpace;\n\n    // Project the near plane ray to the phone model distance.\n    const glm::vec3 cameraSpaceCoordinate \n (worldSpaceNearPlaneCoordinate / NearClip) *\n            (CameraDistance - mTranslation.z);\n\n    const glm::vec3 worldSpaceCoordinate \u003d glm::inverse(mCameraTransform) * cameraSpaceCoordinate;",
      "range": {
