      "writtenOn": "2017-11-14T16:05:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The FOV is calculated (already the case before this change) such that at z\u003d0 the phone can be moved over the full x/y plane defined by the mins/maxes above using the full field of view.  Increasing CameraDistance makes the fov adjust such that the z\u003d0 plane will be the same, but will allow the phone to move a greater distance in the +z direction (towards camera) without going out of the FOV.\n\nCameraDistance\u003d20 made the phone disappear when it moved to z\u003d+4 at the x/y extremes.",
